This substantial industrial complex constructed in the 1970-80s (extended in circa 2002) is a “MUST SEE”. The complex comprises a large single level office component at the Bridge Road frontage, connected to one contiguous warehouse in a U-shape offering abundant amenities for staff and visitors 

The property is located within Keysborough, approximately 27 kilometres from the Melbourne Central Business District. The property is strategically situated on the western side of Bridge Road, being within immediate proximity to the Eastlink interchange on Cheltenham Road. Keysborough is a well-established industrial precinct, historically recognised as a manufacturing and automotive location – but more recently a highly desirable logistics / distribution hub given its accessibility via major arterials and bypasses. Dandenong Railway Station is situated approximately 1.5 Kilometres east of site
